content:
When you’re managing multiple chats or helping a customer in need, having the correct reply available makes your job easier. Einstein Reply Recommendations suggests relevant replies during chat and messaging sessions.

Available in: Lightning Experience, Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Required permissions include Einstein Reply Recommendations User permission set AND Read access to the Quick Text folder containing published replies.

Recommended replies appear in the Einstein Replies component of the Chat and Messaging tabs in the Lightning Service Console. The top of the component shows when the recommendations were last refreshed. To use a reply, click it; to modify, click Edit and Post; or reject by clicking Not Helpful.

When switching between multiple chats, dock the Einstein Replies component to send replies from any console subtab. If you don't see the component, check with your admin that Einstein Reply Recommendations is enabled and Quick Text access and permissions are correct.

Replies aren’t recommended if: published replies were removed or duplicates exist; recommendations are paused; no chat or messaging session is open; responses score below confidence threshold.

Let your admin know of any issues. Did this article solve your issue? Yes/No
title: Einstein Reply Recommendations in Service Cloud
